Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive implementation plan for your Next.js 15+ migration.

# Comprehensive Implementation Plan: Next.js 15+ Portfolio Migration

## Executive Summary

This plan outlines the migration of a static single-page portfolio site to a modern Next.js 15+ application with React 19+, TypeScript, and proper Tailwind CSS integration. The architecture emphasizes type safety, component reusability, and maintainability while preserving all existing functionality.

---

## 1. Project Initialization & Setup

### 1.1 Initial Setup Steps

**Command sequence:**
```bash
# Navigate to project directory
cd /Users/seanreed/PythonProjects/nextjs-projects/my-project-site

# Initialize Next.js 15+ with TypeScript
pnpm create next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --app --no-src --import-alias "@/*"

# Or if directory needs to be empty:
# Create temp directory, initialize there, then move files
```

**Configuration choices during setup:**
- TypeScript: Yes
- ESLint: Yes
- Tailwind CSS: Yes
- `src/` directory: No (use root-level `app/` directory)
- App Router: Yes
- Import alias: `@/*`

### 1.2 Additional Dependencies

```bash
# Install required dependencies
pnpm add clsx tailwind-merge

# Install React 19+ (if not already latest)
pnpm add react@latest react-dom@latest

# Install dev dependencies
pnpm add -D @types/node@latest @types/react@latest @types/react-dom@latest
```

### 1.3 Volta Pinning

After initialization, pin Node.js and pnpm versions:
```bash
volta pin node@22
volta pin pnpm@10
```

This will add to `package.json`:
```json
{
  "volta": {
    "node": "22.x.x",
    "pnpm": "10.x.x"
  }
}
```

---

## 2. Project Structure

### 2.1 Complete File Structure

```
my-project-site/
 app/
    layout.tsx                 # Root layout with metadata
    page.tsx                   # Home page (single-page portfolio)
    fonts/                     # Local fonts (if needed)
    globals.css                # Global styles, Tailwind directives
 components/
    layout/
       Navigation.tsx         # Main navigation component
       MobileMenu.tsx         # Mobile hamburger menu
       Footer.tsx             # Footer component
    sections/
       HeroSection.tsx        # Hero/landing section
       AboutSection.tsx       # About section with skills
       ProjectsSection.tsx    # Projects grid section
       ContactSection.tsx     # Contact cards section
    ui/
       ProjectCard.tsx        # Individual project card
       SkillBadge.tsx         # Skill badge component
       ContactCard.tsx        # Contact card component
       AnimatedSection.tsx    # Wrapper for fade-in animations
       Button.tsx             # Reusable button component
    providers/
        ScrollProvider.tsx     # Context for scroll position tracking
 hooks/
    useScrollPosition.ts       # Track scroll position
    useActiveSection.ts        # Determine active nav section
    useIntersectionObserver.ts # Fade-in animation hook
    useMobileMenu.ts           # Mobile menu state management
 lib/
    utils.ts                   # Utility functions (cn, etc.)
    constants.ts               # App-wide constants
 types/
    index.ts                   # Main type exports
    project.ts                 # Project types
    skill.ts                   # Skill types
    contact.ts                 # Contact types
 data/
    projects.ts                # Project data array
    skills.ts                  # Skills data array
    contacts.ts                # Contact information
 public/
    images/
       project-placeholder.svg
    icons/                     # Local icon assets (if not using library)
 .gitignore
 next.config.ts                 # Next.js configuration
 tailwind.config.ts             # Tailwind configuration
 tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration
 postcss.config.mjs             # PostCSS configuration (auto-generated)
 package.json
 pnpm-lock.yaml
```

---

## 3. Configuration Files

### 3.1 Next.js Configuration (`next.config.ts`)

```typescript
import type { NextConfig } from 'next';

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  // Optimize for static export if needed
  output: 'export', // Remove this if you want server features

  // Image optimization
  images: {
    unoptimized: true, // Required if using output: 'export'
  },

  // Strict mode for better development
  reactStrictMode: true,

  // Disable x-powered-by header
  poweredByHeader: false,
};

export default nextConfig;
```

**Key Decisions:**
- `output: 'export'` for static site generation (local viewing without server)
- Can be removed later if you want to add server-side features
- `images.unoptimized: true` required for static export

### 3.2 TypeScript Configuration (`tsconfig.json`)

The auto-generated config will be good, but ensure these settings:

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "esnext"],
    "allowJs": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "strict": true,
    "noEmit": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "module": "esnext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "incremental": true,
    "plugins": [
      {
        "name": "next"
      }
    ],
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["next-env.d.ts", "**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx", ".next/types/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}
```

### 3.3 Tailwind Configuration (`tailwind.config.ts`)

```typescript
import type { Config } from 'tailwindcss';

