## Critical Files for Implementation

Based on this comprehensive plan, here are the 5 most critical files to create first:

1. **`/app/page.tsx`** - Main entry point that assembles all sections; establishes the overall page structure and component hierarchy.

2. **`/components/layout/Navigation.tsx`** - Most complex component with scroll tracking, active section highlighting, and mobile menu integration; critical for user experience.

3. **`/hooks/useIntersectionObserver.ts`** - Core animation hook used throughout the site; enables fade-in effects on all section components and project cards.

4. **`/types/index.ts`** (with related type files) - Type definitions that enforce type safety across all data structures (projects, skills, contacts); foundational for TypeScript implementation.

5. **`/lib/utils.ts`** - Utility functions (especially `cn()` and `scrollToSection()`) used in nearly every component; critical for Tailwind class management and navigation behavior.

**Honorable mentions:**
- `/data/projects.ts` - Centralizes all project data; easy to update and extend
- `/components/ui/AnimatedSection.tsx` - Wrapper component used extensively for animations
- `/next.config.ts` - Configuration that enables static export for local viewing

